  "description": "Variation of condition 1 and13 of planning permission dated 06 January 2022 (20/05147/FULL) for 'Part demolition of rooftop plant room and creation of a single storey roof extension at Brettenham House to provide B1 office floorspace; associated creation of terraces to the north and south part of the roofs; replacement and relocation of roof plant to basement level at Brettenham House; creation of a new office entrance to Savoy Street at basement level one of Brettenham House; refurbishment of ground floor shopfronts at Brettenham House on Lancaster Place facade; provision of cycle parking and associated facilities in the basement of Brettenham House; replacement of all the external windows and associated facade maintenance and cleaning and associated works at Brettenham House and 1 Lancaster Place'. \rNamely, to allow the following amendments: (1) the two double doors adjacent to the bays on Savoy Street to be relocated to allow for UKPN substation access and fire egress; (2) the louvre on Savoy Street will be replaced by a single fire escape door; (3) the double height roller shutter with wicket door will be replaced by a smaller double door and window on Savoy Street; (4) internal layout amendments at Basement 2 level including relocation of the disabled parking bays to Savoy Street, if the demand arises; and (5) relocation of the accessible entrance to the building.",
